text:
Sheepshead Bay, northward from Shore Boulevard, between Ocean Ave., (left) and Dooley Street(right), showing the fishing boat Evelyn the first boat owned by Captain Jake Martin who in turn has owned the "Glory", "Giralda" and the "Sachem." The first and last are still his boats. At the left on the water is the F.W.I. Lundy Restaurant, next to it is the Sheepshead Ferry house and boats. This line connects the Rockaways. This is a set of three views. In No. three is seen also the steeple of St. Mark's R.C. Church.

July 13, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Sheepshead Bay - Brooklyn - North Shore Blvd. between Ocean Avenue and Dooley Street.
